node.text:
I just wanted to thank everyone for their support. I appreciate all my followers. I hope I can help you to improve your English.
Robin Shaw

#englishcourse #englishfun ##englishteacher #englishwords #englishtips #english

Photo by Robin Shaw on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"IT'S POURING." Pouring is very heavy rain.'.
Photo by Robin Shaw on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"IT'S SPITTING." Spitting is very light rain, rain that you can barely feel.'.
Photo by Robin Shaw on July 21, 2021. May be an image of pizza and text that says '"IT'S DRIZZLING." Drizzling is more than spitting, less than raining.'.

Photo by Robin Shaw on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"LET'S STAY INSIDE UNTIL THE RAIN LETS UP." The phrasal verb let up means stop completely, or at least become slower. Say this sentence when want to wait until the rain stops.'.
Photo by Robin Shaw on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"IT'S BEEN RAINING ON AND OFF ALL DAY." On and off means starting & stopping, then starting again over a period of time.'.
Photo by Robin Shaw on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'WE GOT CAUGHT IN A DOWNPOUR." A downpour is a sudden, unexpected, heavy rain, or a lot of rain in a shor period of time.'.
